<?xml version='1.0' encoding='UTF-8'?>
<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-11-14T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-11-14T00:00:00-05:00" n="8" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d8">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">
                            <persName corresp="#p_WW1">Woodrow Wilson</persName> Papers</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">President <persName corresp="#p_WW1" type="from">Wilson</persName> to the British Prime Minister</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_LGD1" type="to"><hi rend="italic">Lloyd
                                George</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">[<placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                                </placeName>,] <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-11-14">14
                                    November, 1918</date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>May I not express my sincere admiration of the admirable temper and
                            purpose of your address of the eleventh [<hi rend="italic">twelfth</hi>]
                            just reproduced <pb facs="0074" n="4" xml:id="pg_4"/> in part in our
                                papers.<note n="3a" xml:id="d8fn3a">Full text printed in the London
                                    <hi rend="italic">Times</hi>, Nov. 13, 1918, p. 9.</note> It is
                            delightful to be made aware of such community of thought and counsel in
                            approaching the high and difficult task now awaiting us.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <persName corresp="#p_WW1">
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Woodrow Wilson</hi>
                                </persName>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>